  "mission":[
    "The mission of the City Clerk's office is to accept, file, record, and maintain all municipal records. The City Clerk publishes the agenda for all City Council meetings, records all Council and related Mayoral actions, and edits and compiles the minutes"
  ],
  "description_of_services":[
    "Services to the public include the sale of various licenses and permits, notarizing and attesting to documents, and filing, recording, and copying papers in the custody of the Clerk. Services to City government consist of providing informational resources and technical assistance, administration of oaths of office, attestation of various legal papers, custody of records, and administration of the state's open meeting law. The Archives Commission oversees the protection of City records, files, and other items of historic interest."
  ],
